<br>
Absolved is now accepting a small number of applications for membership.  But before I get into that, I'm sure you'd like to know a little about the guild itself. <br>
<br>
Absolved is formed under the notion that having a &quot;close-knit&quot; atmosphere and that being a successful raiding guild are not mutually exclusive. <br>
<br>
In order to best explain what our plans are, I've come up with a sort of road map, which I hope will work out better then the one in the middle east.<br>
<br>
Short term, we're trying to establish a solid core. These players - I &quot;envision&quot; 12-18, will have plenty of time to really get to know each other - this group will be our foundation.  #1 REQUIREMENT IS PERSONAL CHARACTER!  I want folks who are fun, patient, dedicated, and skilled, who are willing to put in a few extra hours on a weekend. Face it, these are the types of folks you yourself would want to be guilded with.  I'm just putting them into words.  And, in my time here on Firiona Vie, I dont think I'll have a problem finding people like this.<br>
<br>
Medium term, enjoy playing with each other.  Continue to bolster our ranks into my membership goal of roughly 60 active, skilled players.  Continue to advance and establish those interpersonal relationships that make this game so damned fun, and so damned addictive.<br>
<br>
My long term goal for Absolved is to give people an home on Firiona Vie that they can be immensely proud of - a guild that, while goal oriented, supports peoples schedules and is not so time demanding that peoples real life families and careers have to suffer.  <br>
<br>
I'll end this right here with one last thing.. I want to have fun.. and I want to have fun with a group of people I can call friends. Everything else is second to that.<br>
<br>
Very sincerely,<br>
<br>
Daggz Nabbit<br>
Rogue of the Vale<br>
Leader of Absolved<br>
<br>
